rn it from this word כשב <i>keshev</i>, the sheep, that it says by the שלמים <i>shelamim</i>, which we assume to be extra. כשהוא אומר אם כשב <i>ke-she-hu omer im keshev</i>, if it's a sheep, להביא פסח שעברה שנתו <i>le-havi pesach she-avrah shenaso</i>, to tell you that not only are we talking about a פסח <i>Pesach</i> that you burn the fat tail, but we're talking about things that used to be a פסח <i>Pesach</i> have a הלכה <i>halacha</i> of a שלמים <i>shelamim</i>. So for example, the פסח <i>Pesach</i> its year is over, it's more than one year old, the פסח <i>Pesach</i> has to be within one year. ושלמים הבאים מחמת פסח <i>u-shelamim ha-ba'im machmas pesach</i>, and שלמים <i>shelamim</i> that come because of the פסח <i>Pesach</i>. לכל מצוות שלמים <i>le-khol mitzvos shelamim</i>, that they're treated as, I'll discuss that category in a minute, they're treated as a full שלמים <i>shelamim</i>. What does it mean? שטעונים סמיכה <i>she-te'unim semichah</i>, you do with them everything you'd do with a שלמים <i>shelamim</i>. You do סמיכה <i>semichah</i>, ונסכים <i>u-nesachim</i>, and the wine. Again, you don't do this by a פסח <i>Pesach</i>, but you do this by when the פסח <i>Pesach</i> transforms into a שלמים <i>shelamim</i>. ותנופת חזה ושוק <i>u-tenufas chaze ve-shok</i>, you wave the חזה <i>chaze</i> and the שוק <i>shok</i>. That's what you do with a פסח <i>Pesach</i> when it becomes a שלמים <i>shelamim</i>. כשהוא אומר <i>ke-she-hu omer</i>, and then the פסוק <i>pasuk</i> says, ואם עז <i>ve-im ez</i>, but if you're bringing a goat for your שלמים <i>shelamim</i>, הפסיק העניין <i>hifsik ha-inyan</i>, that interrupts it. ללמד על העז <i>le-lammed al ha-ez</i>, that if you're bringing a goat שאינה טעונה אליה <i>she-einah te'unah alyah</i>. You don't apply what the תורה <i>Torah</i> said before by the sheep, you don't give a fat tail of the goat. It's always quite fascinating that the גמרא <i>Gemara</i> have to learn out that you don't give a fat tail of a goat. Goats don't have